5:
You want me to help out in Shibuya
tomorrow? ME?
9:
Yep. Our office over there is
swamped because of Halloween.
11:
We got a lot of requests for you to
head over since you know Shibuya
well.
15:
...Hmph, I guess if you're okay with it,
then I am too.
19:
It's totally fine if you don't want to.
You're allowed to say no.
26:
A bunch of people are gonna throw
a fit if I show up. That's all.
34: ...Duh. You don't have to tell me.
42:
Ugh, they're going all out with the
partying. Wish that was me.
46:
It's plenty fun just watching from the
side, though.
51:
Aaaand there you go again, always
with the good-girl response.
55:
Hey! You can party, but keep the
property destruction to a minimum.
58:
Can't believe I'm stuck being a
glorified babysitter.
63:
You can't fault them for cutting
loose. Everyone's pretty stressed,
even with things going good with
the Palpebrans—
67:
Like hell I'm believing a single word
coming outta these punks!
69:
I know they used to be Aegis
assholes! There's no hiding it from
me!
71:
That's no reason to blame them
without proof!
73:
I-it's fine, you don't have to defend
us—
76:
We'll take it from here. Guild reps,
reporting for duty. Can someone tell
me what's going on?
82:
These guys stole from me! Slipped in
during all the partying, thinking they
were being clever!
84: Like I said, you don't have proof!
90:
W-we didn't do it! I swear, we were
just passing by when he grabbed us!
93:
We'll need to take statements from
everyone here. Whatever the truth,
we'll get to the bottom of it—
96:
Yeah? How do I know you're not
covering for your friends?
98:
I've seen this girl around! She used
to be an Aegis punk too! You expect
me to trust her?!
101:
Excuse me? Say that to me again. I
dare you.
113:
Listen, I don't play favorites. But if
you want my honest opinion? These
guys probably didn't do it.
115:
From what I remember about them,
they're the type to fess up and say
sorry when they mess up.
119:
Not that that matters! I'm here on
Guild business, so we'll be doing
things by the book.
121:
If you want, I can even get a
different Guild member to handle
the case—
126:
Pardon me. Does this item belong to
you?
131: Keira? What are you doing here?
135:
I apprehended a thief not long ago.
They confessed that they stole items
from this store, so I came to return
was stolen.
140:
Well, aren't you lucky. You got your
stuff back! Still, we have to file a
report, so you'll have to come with
us to the office.
146:
Urgh... What a total pain in the ass
that was!
154:
...What're you grinning about? You're
grossing me out.
158:
Am I grinning? I didn't even notice. I
guess I was just happy...
170:
Thank Keira, not me. I didn't do
much.
173:
That's not true. You did a lot for us,
even when you didn't have to.
179:
...I was also wondering... Could I go
through with what I asked the other
day?
182:
Oh, the Guild stuff? Yeah, have a
seat.
186:
You'll just have to fill out this
paperwork. I can walk you through it
and answer any questions that
come up.
189:
...What're you freezing up for?
Changed your mind?
192:
Ah, no, I was just... surprised. You're
actually pretty serious about your
job.
199:
I can confirm that Hikawa's a hard
worker.
202:
I really am sorry about calling you a
poser the other day...
205:
She's changed, right? Even you can
see it.
214:
Shut UP! No one asked you to open
your big stupid mouth!
